0.0.1.0/24 on eth8 (connected)\n- Reachability summary:\n  - Many host-to-host pings successful (loss_percent 0.0), but pc_0_1-originated tests are \"unknown\".\n\nConfidence and notes\n- Confidence that the rest of the fabric is healthy (BGP sessions up, routes present, host-to-host pings across fabric successful): high.\n- Confidence that pc_0_1 is isolated due to a local link-level issue between pc_0_1 and leaf_router_0_1: high (direct packet counter evidence on both endpoints).\n- The missing default route on pc_0_1 is definite (observed) and would prevent remote connectivity even if the link were up; however the immediate cause of zero counters is best explained by physical/data-link disconnection.\n\nNo mitigations included in this report. If you want, I can next run targeted tests (ARP table checks, ethtool on the interfaces, or bring up/down checks) to further narrow the L1/L2 cause.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 34831, "output_tokens": 3089, "total_tokens": 37920, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8832}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1792}}}
